More Hits for More Damage = Better Aggro <p><div align="center"><embed width="468" height="148" src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/amplified/SWSig.swf"></div><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udaredox.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daredox</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/02 11:01:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: primal question</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure if this is right so correct me if I'm wrong... but doesn't buffing somebody that has aggro on a mob, give you aggro too? I know that when me and some friends were messing around in seb, I was tanking the seb protector, he was down to about 50% health, and I never lost aggro to the rogue or bard. Then the cleric cast group aego on us, and he got aggro to the mob immediately, not sure if it works the same with Avatar though. <p><img src="http://knightsoftheoldcode.homestead.com/files/slamminn_s_sig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usmushums.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smushums</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 1339<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/02 11:04:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: primal question</span><hr size=1> yea, some buffs give a lot of agro, especially ones like rune<br>
<br>
avatar isnt one of em though.  i've never noticed a proc turning a head before <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukimagure.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kimagure</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/02 11:17:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: primal question</span><hr size=1> The reason the cleric got aggro from casting group aego is because aego is a spell that gives HP.  It's sort of like a healing spell aggro.  Then, because it was group aego, the cleric was counted as giving health to all members of the group.  Hence, major aggro added to mob's hate list.<br>
<br>
Any buff that gives HP or the appearance of HP (like rune) will give a good bit of aggro.  Imagine healing spells as doing damage to the mob, via negative damage to the person being healed.  i.e. Healing for 4k hp is similar to doing 4k damage to the mob all at once. <p><Table Style='Filter: Alpha(Opacity=100, FinishOpacity=50, Style=2, StartX=85, FinishX=20, StartY=0, FinishY=0)'><B><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6495" target="magelo"><Font Color=#FFCC33 Size=3 Face=Times New Roman, Helvetica>Rula - warh0bbit, esq.</Font></a><br><a href="http://www.shattered-sorcery.com/blight/" target="Blight"><Font Color=CC00FF><i>&#60Blight&#62, Vazaelle</i></Font></a><br></B></Table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ualien1099.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alien1099</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 490<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/02 2:22:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/~mondo/aliensm.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: primal question</span><hr size=1> It does not decrease your miss rate. <p><p><font face="verdana, arial" size="-2"><u><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6885" target=top>Gerald Swiftblades</a></u> [<a href="http://" target=top><i></i></a>]<br>
      <b>Human Warlord</b><br>
