</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unortherner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Northerner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/02 9:38:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/sjgardner/Images/celeris2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: primal question</span><hr size=1> I don't have Primal (and I am actually a Rogue) but I've had several hunting groups where I've gotten Avatar as a regular buff through the night.  On mid/upper 50s Mobs in CT I gain 19-22% in dps, although I'll be the first to say that there is ample room for error in the few samples I have.  As stated above though, attack has nothing to do with the hit-miss ratio.<br>
